1
00:00:03,360 --> 00:00:05,160
Although resting can keep your condition

2
00:00:05,160 --> 00:00:06,480
from worsening quickly,

3
00:00:06,480 --> 00:00:08,080
you only have a few years left.

4
00:00:08,080 --> 00:00:09,480
If you neglect your rest

5
00:00:09,480 --> 00:00:10,360
because of work again,

6
00:00:10,360 --> 00:00:12,220
you could be in danger at any time.

7
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:15,600
Thank you.

8
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:23,200
Come in, 5533016.

9
00:00:24,280 --> 00:00:27,000
Captain Li, here's the case summary for Guangnan and Guixi.

10
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:28,200
Ma Guodong didn't sign it.

11
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:29,920
Ma has dropped out of this case.

12
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:31,580
You can just sign it yourself.

13
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:32,320
Why?

14
00:00:34,040 --> 00:00:35,600
Ma has left the frontline.

15
00:00:35,880 --> 00:00:37,200
I arranged a long vacation for him.

16
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:39,600
He'll be transferred to a clerical post when he returns.

17
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:41,720
A long vacation? What about the case?

18
00:00:41,720 --> 00:00:43,240
What reason does he have to take a leave?

19
00:00:43,240 --> 00:00:44,360
He is sick.

20
00:00:45,240 --> 00:00:47,040
About Ma... Understood.

21
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:04,000
Sign it before you leave.

22
00:01:04,319 --> 00:01:05,200
Sign what?

23
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:06,680
You are in charge of this case from now on.

24
00:01:06,680 --> 00:01:08,120
All right. Sign it.

25
00:01:08,120 --> 00:01:09,650
I'll take care of this case.

26
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:21,960
You are really something, Ma Guodong.

27
00:01:21,960 --> 00:01:23,240
Just because of a little conflict,

28
00:01:23,240 --> 00:01:25,320
you made up a sick leave to step back.

29
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:27,060
It must be hard for you.

30
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:28,120
Okay, okay, okay.

31
00:01:28,120 --> 00:01:30,120
Whatever you say. I made it up.

32
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:46,240
Although resting can keep your condition from worsening quickly,

33
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:47,800
you don't have many years left.

34
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:50,200
If you neglect your rest for work again,

35
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:51,720
you might...

36
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:12,090
1998.

37
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:18,200
Aiyuan.

38
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:20,280
Aiyuan.

39
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:22,560
I have good news for you.

40
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:24,160
Wait, no.

41
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:25,000
Two.

42
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:28,680
The doctor says I'm in good health,

43
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:30,240
recovering well,

44
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:31,360
and have no aftereffects.

45
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:33,040
The second piece of good news...

46
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:34,000
I'll do it.

47
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Have a seat first.

48
00:02:35,079 --> 00:02:35,760
The second good news,

49
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:37,360
I must announce it properly.

50
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:39,290
Did you add salt?

51
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:40,560
No.

52
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:52,520
Hurry up.

53
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:54,000
Got it.

54
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,360
It needs to be fully cooked.

55
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:05,680
The second good news.

56
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:10,680
Look.

57
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,060
Does it look alike?

58
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:18,440
Address: No. 159, Caojia Brigade, Yongding County, Dongwan City.

59
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:19,100
Can I use it?

60
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:20,640
Of course you can.

61
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:24,040
We don't have money to buy a household register yet.

62
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:25,040
But this woman,

63
00:03:25,480 --> 00:03:26,360
I know her.

64
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:28,960
She is seriously ill and will be hospitalized for a while.

65
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:30,690
She won't even need her ID card.

66
00:03:31,079 --> 00:03:32,680
So just use it without worry.

67
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,200
What's wrong?

68
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:41,000
Why do you still seem unhappy?

69
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:42,760
Don't worry.

70
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:45,280
The doctor said I'm fine.

71
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:47,920
Look.

72
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,440
With this,

73
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:51,960
we can truly start a new life.

74
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:54,960
Just like you said, you can go out to buy things,

75
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:56,640
or even use it to find a job.

76
00:03:58,960 --> 00:03:59,840
I see

77
00:04:00,160 --> 00:04:01,960
a lot of people are learning to drive lately.

78
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:03,220
Many of them are women.

79
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,360
Let's learn it too.

80
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:07,240
We can travel everywhere in the future.

81
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:09,440
You drive, and I'll read the map for you.

82
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:14,600
Let's eat first.

83
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:17,160
Okay.

84
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:36,060
The vegetables are very fresh today.

85
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:45,920
Wei.

86
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:47,880
Please sign this later.

87
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:49,640
We're going to get lunch.

88
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:50,320
Let's go.

89
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:53,280
Ran, what brings you here?

90
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,260
I came to run an errand,

91
00:04:56,840 --> 00:05:00,000
and dropped by to see us.

92
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:03,160
Are you coming to the cafeteria with us?

93
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:04,360
No, I'm not hungry.

94
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:05,680
Okay, we'll head out first.

95
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:06,080
Let's go.

96
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:06,960
Bye, Ran.

97
00:05:06,960 --> 00:05:07,840
Yeah, bye.

98
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:10,220
Close the door.

99
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:11,040
Right.

100
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:17,410
Didn't go eat with them?

101
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:18,740
I'm not too hungry.

102
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:22,560
Well,

103
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:24,680
how is your master doing now?

104
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:26,360
When I visited him last time,

105
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:28,160
he said he was doing quite well.

106
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:29,600
He transferred to a desk job,

107
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:31,530
so it's not as exhausting anymore.

108
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:34,659
Do you need him for something?

109
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:36,320
Nothing.

110
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:40,080
I'm going to see him later.

111
00:05:40,080 --> 00:05:41,480
Do you want to come along?

112
00:05:44,159 --> 00:05:45,480
I haven't finished the paperwork yet.

113
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:46,740
You can go by yourself.

114
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:05,760
Yinuo, what do you want to eat tonight?

115
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:08,280
Ice cream? Ice cream is not good.

116
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:09,960
It's too cold and bad for your stomach.

117
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:11,420
Can we eat something else?

118
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:15,330
What else do you want to eat?

119
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:17,800
You want ice cream?

120
00:06:18,440 --> 00:06:21,200
Okay, we'll eat whatever Yinuo wants.

121
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:23,260
All right? I'll let you eat your fill.

122
00:06:24,040 --> 00:06:24,570
Let's go.

123
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:29,240
You're not cold, are you?

124
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:30,410
Let's go.

125
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,040
Officer Ma.

126
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:34,760
Who are you?

127
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:36,560
My name is Yao Guoqing.

128
00:06:36,640 --> 00:06:38,300
I am Nuannuan's grandfather.

129
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:40,140
Yao Shufen is my daughter.

130
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:41,840
I need to talk to you.

131
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:50,460
These past few months.

132
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:52,720
I've been to almost all the cities and surrounding areas

133
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:54,580
where they've committed crimes.

134
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:56,880
But I don't know where it will be next.

135
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,260
I'm afraid I can't help

136
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:04,640
with this case.

137
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:07,560
I've been transferred from the frontline

138
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:08,760
to do clerical work.

139
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:11,880
I also promised Yinuo

140
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:15,360
that I would spend all my time with her.

141
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:17,440
When she's happy,

142
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:19,280
I can feel at ease.

143
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:22,200
Uncle, go catch the bad guys.

144
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:24,680
Yinuo doesn't need you to stay with her.

145
00:07:29,960 --> 00:07:36,960
Look at these cities, Changzhou, Dongwan, and Guixi.

146
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:41,040
They are all very close to the city where they committed their last crime.

147
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:43,170
So I guess it's possible in any of them.

148
00:07:44,840 --> 00:07:46,770
It seems you've put a lot of thought

149
00:07:47,320 --> 00:07:48,640
into this case.

150
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:56,760
Here are some notes I made.

151
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,280
Take them.

152
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:12,520
You should go home first. Nuannuan needs your company more.

153
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:27,680
Thank you, Officer Ma.

154
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:30,660
Don't thank me.

155
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:33,159
I didn't do anything for you.

156
00:08:33,919 --> 00:08:37,360
If you want to thank someone, thank Yinuo.

157
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:58,080
My passion is like a fire,

158
00:08:58,480 --> 00:09:01,480
burning up the entire desert.

159
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:05,320
Hello, Jiawei.

160
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,330
What time tomorrow?

161
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:09,440
What do you mean 5:00?

162
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,520
More sugarcane,

163
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:13,960
and make it a bit cheaper, okay?

164
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:27,440
Aiyuan.

165
00:09:37,280 --> 00:09:38,000
Come here.

166
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:43,880
You made money.

167
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,890
This is what I earned today.

168
00:09:46,280 --> 00:09:47,200
Usual rules.

169
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:49,160
You're still in charge of our money.

170
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:50,890
I'll keep this for stocking up.

171
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:54,200
What's wrong?

172
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:59,080
I just see you leaving early and coming home late every day,

173
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:00,280
and it's quite tough.

174
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:02,000
How about I go out and find a job too?

175
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,880
I'm not tired.

176
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:06,480
You just stay home and count the money,

177
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:07,810
and I'll earn it.

178
00:10:08,880 --> 00:10:10,680
I'm actually quite free at home.

179
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:14,280
If I go out to work, I can also help share your burden.

180
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:18,760
Do you really want to work that much?

181
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:24,600
Alright.

182
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:26,280
Then promise me.

183
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:28,400
You are so pretty,

184
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:29,760
and you have many skills.

185
00:10:29,760 --> 00:10:31,020
You even know English.

186
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:32,760
If we're looking,

187
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:34,290
we should find a decent job.

188
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:36,760
Don't run into those messy people again,

189
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:37,280
okay?

190
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:39,480
Of course.

191
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:42,960
Okay, let's go eat noodles at the village entrance.

192
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:43,760
Let's eat out.

193
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:45,320
Hurry up.

194
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:50,680
Ms. Liu,

195
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:52,800
if the salary is fine,

196
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:54,560
you can start work tomorrow.

197
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:56,540
Okay. Thank you, Manager.

198
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:58,360
Then go back and prepare.

199
00:10:58,360 --> 00:11:00,320
I'll submit your profile to HR.

200
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:01,800
Okay? Okay.

201
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:12,840
How did it go?

202
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:13,760
I got it.

203
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:14,640
Success!

204
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,280
This place is so fancy.

205
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:37,280
Aiyuan,

206
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:40,320
is this your work uniform?

207
00:11:40,560 --> 00:11:41,400
Does it look good?

208
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:42,320
It looks great.

209
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:44,000
You start work tomorrow.

210
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,400
I got you something.

211
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:47,840
What is it?

212
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:48,760
Sit down first.

213
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:54,640
Why are you being so mysterious?

214
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:08,360
Do you like it?

215
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:09,760
A phone?

216
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:11,480
For me?

217
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:12,680
For you.

218
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:15,480
But this is way too expensive.

219
00:12:15,880 --> 00:12:17,160
It's not expensive.

220
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:19,960
It's second-hand. Just take it.

221
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:22,130
It's not easy for you to make money.

222
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:24,160
You should probably return it.

223
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:25,560
I can't return it.

224
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:26,680
You know what?

225
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:29,600
When I asked the store owner to download that English song today,

226
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:30,760
the one you really like,

227
00:12:30,760 --> 00:12:33,000
I was too clueless to know the name.

228
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:34,880
He spent ages searching and putting it in.

229
00:12:34,880 --> 00:12:35,720
If I try to return it now,

230
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:37,450
he'll definitely get mad at me.

231
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:38,280
Just keep it.

232
00:12:44,160 --> 00:12:45,680
First day of work today.

233
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:47,200
How do you feel?

234
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:50,000
I'm happy. Very happy.

235
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:50,800
I'm happy too.

236
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:53,000
Are you nervous?

237
00:12:53,280 --> 00:12:54,680
Be careful going downhill.

238
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:55,480
Just a bit nervous.
